  "title": "WORKPLACE SAFETY & HEALTH OFFICER",
  "description": "<p><strong>WORKPLACE SAFETY &amp; HEALTH OFFICER (WSHO)</strong></p>\n<p>(Building Construction)</p>\n<p>Responsibilities :</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop,implement, enforce and maintain safety policies, procedures and      regulations to ensure site compliance with prevailing MOM safety acts and      Regulations etc</li>\n  <li>Enforce and ensure all sites are complied with Workplace, Safety &amp; Health Acts</li>\n  <li>Provides Safety Advice guidance, consultation, briefing, training and supports on all aspects to the operators, site staff and workers/subcontractors to ensure proper execution of assigned tasks</li>\n  <li>Conduct and enforce WSH and In-House rules and regulations, inspections of safety work processes and follow up corrective actions where necessary to ensure workplace safety and compliance with approved Safe Work Practices (SWP)</li>\n  <li>Conduct investigations of all safety infringements and accidents and to propose or recommend remedial actions to minimize the risk</li>\n  <li>Liaise and coordinate with relevant Authorities on all safety issues</li>\n  <li>ISO documentation &amp; administration</li>\n  <li>Record, compile &amp; submit weekly report</li>\n  <li>To perform and responsible for all others related or ad-hoc duties as and when assigned by the Project Team, your immediate Superior including any related matters not mentioned above</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements :</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Certificate of Registration by MOM</li>\n  <li>Degree or Diploma in Safety</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of working experience as WSHO (MOM registered) in local construction industry especially in HDB / Commercial projects and private developments etc</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
